                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War 1939/1224: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-10T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 10, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>249. Reference your 39, January 3, 9 p.m. For the American members of the London
                    Political Warfare Coordinating Committee:</p>
                <p>We feel that it would be undesirable to take this matter up at the present time
                    with the view to obtaining a decision and that it would be preferable to adhere
                    to the position set forth in the Department’s 8267 of December 31, 7 p.m.<note
                        n="33" xml:id="d1088fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1943v03#pg_853">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1943, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 853</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
